The Gods Are Real (RimWorld Mod)
A RimWorld mod that introduces a dynamic, per-pawn "Favor" system tied to Ideology. Pawns are no longer just followers—their devotion is a measurable, shifting resource that determines their relationship with their deity.

How It Works
The Favor System
Favor tracking: Each pawn's favor level is tracked in real-time, ranging from -100 (Divine Wrath) to +100 (Divine Grace).

Decay: Favor is a fleeting resource. Without active worship, it will naturally decay toward zero over time.

Divine Hediff: Your standing with your deity is reflected in the Divine Touch health condition (Hediff), which updates dynamically based on your current favor level.

How to Gain Favor
Rituals: The primary engine for favor. A "Spectacular" ritual can grant massive favor boosts, while failed rituals or the presence of heretics (non-believers) will result in penalties.

Prayer: Actively praying at a Stele provides a steady, reliable drip of favor over time.

Daily Devotion: Positive thoughts tied to your Ideology's precepts will provide a small, constant increase in favor, rewarding pawns who live according to their faith.

Consequences
Divine Grace: High favor rewards the faithful with mood buffs.

Divine Wrath: Low favor—caused by failed rituals, heretical behavior, or lack of worship—will result in severe mood penalties and the "Divine Wrath" state.

Conversion: If a pawn changes their Ideology, their favor is reset to ensure a fresh start with their new faith.

Features for Testers
Debug Mode: Users with Dev Mode enabled have access to a dedicated settings window to manually add/remove favor, force prayer, and check Ideology-wide favor statistics.

